workflow.name: Automate client renewal alerts from GoHighLevel to Gmail, Slack & Google Sheets
workflow.description:
## Description
Streamline client retention and contract renewals by automatically identifying expiring accounts, sending personalized reminder emails, and notifying account managers through Slack. This workflow ensures timely outreach, improved renewal rates, and centralized tracking ‚Äî without manual effort. üîÅüìßüìÖ

## What This Template Does
- Triggers daily at 9 AM to check for contracts expiring within 10 days. ‚è∞
- Fetches all client records from GoHighLevel CRM. üóÇÔ∏è
- Validates client data to ensure required custom fields (Contract End Date & Account Manager) are available. üß©
- Filters expiring contracts and formats key client details (name, email, expiry date). üîç
- Sends renewal reminder emails to clients using Gmail. üíå
- Notifies account managers in Slack with full client and renewal details. üí¨
- Generates a summary report of total reminders sent and execution status. üìã
- Logs all reminders and timestamps into Google Sheets for performance tracking. üìä

## Key Benefits
‚úÖ Never miss renewal deadlines again
 ‚úÖ Improve client retention and satisfaction
 ‚úÖ Reduce manual tracking and follow-up work
 ‚úÖ Keep account managers informed in real-time
 ‚úÖ Maintain a clear audit trail of renewal activities

## Features
- Automated daily scheduling (9 AM trigger)
- GoHighLevel integration for client data
- Dynamic filtering for contracts expiring within 10 days
- Gmail email automation for personalized messages
- Slack notifications for internal visibility
- Google Sheets logging for analytics and reporting

## Requirements
- GoHighLevel account with access to Contacts API
- Custom fields: Contract End Date and Account Manager
- Gmail account with OAuth2 credentials
- Slack Bot token with chat:write permission
- Google Sheets OAuth2 credentials

## Target Audience
- Account management and client success teams
- Agencies handling multiple client contracts
- Businesses with recurring subscriptions or service renewals
- Teams wanting automated retention workflows

## Step-by-Step Setup Instructions
- Connect your GoHighLevel account and ensure contract-related custom fields are configured.
- Set your Slack channel ID where renewal notifications will be sent.
- Connect Gmail for automated client communication.
- Link Google Sheets for centralized renewal logging.
- Adjust reminder window in the code node (daysUntilExpiry <= 10) as per your needs.
- Test the workflow once manually, then enable scheduling for automation.

workflow.name: Automate Client Renewal Alerts from GoHighLevel to Gmail and Slack

parameters.content:
## üîÑ Client Retention Renewal Reminder Workflow

Automatically identifies clients with contracts expiring within 10 days and sends personalized renewal reminders.

### What This Workflow Does:
- **Runs daily at 9 AM** to check for expiring contracts
- **Fetches all contacts** from GoHighLevel CRM
- **Filters clients** whose contracts expire in 0-10 days
- **Sends renewal emails** to clients via Gmail
- **Notifies account managers** via Slack
- **Logs all activities** to Google Sheets for tracking

### Business Benefits:
- ‚úÖ Never miss a renewal opportunity
- ‚úÖ Improve client retention rates
- ‚úÖ Automate manual follow-up tasks
- ‚úÖ Track renewal campaign effectiveness

### Requirements:
- GoHighLevel account with custom fields:
  - Contract End Date field
  - Account Manager field
- Gmail account for sending emails
- Slack workspace for notifications
- Google Sheets for logging

## ‚è∞ Schedule Trigger Setup

Runs daily at 9:00 AM server time.

**Configuration:**
- Cron: `0 9 * * *`
- Frequency: Every day
- Time: 9:00 AM

**Why 9 AM?**
Early morning execution ensures:
- Emails arrive during business hours
- Account managers have full day to respond
- Prevents weekend/holiday issues

## üì• Fetch Contacts from CRM

**Setup Instructions:**
1. Connect your GoHighLevel account
2. Set limit to 50 (or adjust based on needs)
3. Ensure API permissions include contact read access

**Required Custom Fields:**
- Contract End Date (Date field)
- Account Manager (Text field)

**Note:** Increase limit if you have more than 50 active clients

## üîç Validate Data Quality

Ensures contacts have custom fields before processing.

**Why This Matters:**
- Prevents errors in downstream nodes
- Filters out incomplete contact records
- Improves workflow reliability

## üéØ Filter Expiring Contracts

**Logic:**
- Finds Contract End Date field
- Calculates days until expiry
- Filters: 0-10 days remaining

**Customization:**
Change `daysUntilExpiry <= 10` to adjust reminder window:
- 7 days = 1 week notice
- 14 days = 2 weeks notice
- 30 days = 1 month notice

**Important:** Update field IDs to match YOUR GoHighLevel custom fields

## üìß Send Client Email

**Setup:**
1. Connect Gmail account
2. Replace recipient with: `={{ $json.email }}`
3. Customize email template

**Email Variables:**
- `firstName` - Client first name
- `lastName` - Client last name
- `contractEndDate` - Formatted expiry date
- `companyName` - Company name

**Best Practice:** Test email with your own address first

parameters.message:
=Hi {{ $json.firstName }} {{ $json.lastName }},

This is a friendly reminder that your contract with us is set to expire on {{ $json.contractEndDate }}.

We'd love to continue working with you! Please let us know if you'd like to discuss renewal options.

Your account manager will be reaching out shortly.

Best regards,
Your Team

parameters.content:
## üì¢ Slack Team Notification

**Setup:**
1. Connect Slack workspace
2. Select channel for renewal alerts
3. Customize message format

**Recommended Channels:**
- #renewals
- #account-management
- #sales-alerts

**Note:** Ensure all account managers have access to the selected channel

## üìä Generate Summary Report

Creates execution summary with:
- Total reminders sent
- Timestamp of execution
- Success status

**Used for:**
- Tracking workflow performance
- Logging to Google Sheets
- Debugging issues

## üìù Log to Google Sheets

**Setup:**
1. Create a Google Sheet for tracking
2. Add columns: summary, totalRemindersSent, timestamp, message
3. Connect your Google account
4. Select your spreadsheet and sheet

The IF node can be used to implement binary conditional logic in your workflow. You can set up one-to-many conditions to evaluate each item of data being inputted into the node. That data will either evaluate to TRUE or FALSE and route out of the node accordingly.

This node has multiple types of conditions: Bool, String, Number, and Date & Time.

data.details: The Code node allows you to execute JavaScript in your workflow.

The Filter node can be used to filter items based on a condition. If the condition is met, the item will be passed on to the next node. If the condition is not met, the item will be omitted. Conditions can be combined together by AND(meet all conditions), or OR(meet at least one condition).
